RANCHO RED tracked the early pace while on a hold, raced three wide into the turn, came four wide into the stretch and did not threaten. DARK MYSTERY lacked early speed, chased four wide along the turn, raced four then five wide into the stretch and did not factor. COUNT ASHER was away in good order and tracked the early pace outside of runners, lost position into the turn, was eased through the stretch, walked off under his own power and was reported to have bled when pulled up.

PASS THE BATON reserved early, worked out an inside trip while gradually moving into contention, awaited room through the far turn then slipped through a big opening along the rail, took a short lead, finished well but was overtaken by CRYPTO MAN in deep stretch while well clear of the third finisher.
